{
  "texts": [
    "Afterwards, we synthesise the co-occurrence analysis and TM results, and therefore propose the conceptual framework of TM application in Fig. 8.",
    "Results as shown in Fig. 6, evidence that data mining, topic model, statistics, semantics, latent Dirichlet allocation, information retrieval, natural language processing, neural topic model, word2vec, structural topic modeling, recurrent neural network, speech recognition, scientometrics, public policy, COVID-19, social media, article, risk assessment, content analysis, misinformation, vaccine, medical informatics, computational biology, big data, recommender systems, image processing, computer vision, and social networking (online) are the dominant terms.",
    "Furthermore, we observed that these terms are grouped into 5 clusters, Cluster 1 (446 items), Cluster 2 (298 items), Cluster 3 (250 items), Cluster 4 (4 items) and Cluster 5 (2 items).",
    "In order to understand the network, we interpret the main items in the three main clusters (Cluster 1-3) attaining the higher number of links, occurrences and total link strength.",
    "For example, the item Topic Model in Cluster 1 has 948 links, 21,914 total link strength and the number of occurrences is 3131.This item is associated with other items in the same cluster such as statistics, Bayesian networks, information retrieval systems."
  ]
}